50  static Sdl()
51  {
52  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.OSX))
53  {
54  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
55  {
56  case Architecture.Arm64:
57  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.dylib", NativeGraphic.osx_arm64_sdl2);
58  break;
59  case Architecture.X64:
60  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.dylib", NativeGraphic.osx_x64_sdl2);
61  break;
62  }
63  }
64 
65  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
66  {
67  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
68  {
69  case Architecture.Arm64:
70  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.dll", NativeGraphic.win_arm64_sdl2);
71  break;
72  case Architecture.X86:
73  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.dll", NativeGraphic.win_x86_sdl2);
74  break;
75  case Architecture.X64:
76  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.dll", NativeGraphic.win_x64_sdl2);
77  break;
78  }
79  }
80 
81  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Linux))
82  {
83  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
84  {
85  case Architecture.Arm64:
86  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.so", NativeGraphic.linux_arm64_sdl2);
87  break;
88  case Architecture.X64:
89  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("sdl2.so", NativeGraphic.linux_x64_sdl2);
90  break;
91  }
92  }
93  }

1344  #region UTF8 Marshaling
1345 
1346  /* Used for stack allocated string marshaling. */
1352  internal static int Utf8Size(string str)
1353  {
1354  if (str == null)
1355  {
1356  return 0;
1357  }
1358 
1359  return str.Length * 4 + 1;
1360  }
1361 
1369  internal static unsafe byte* Utf8Encode(string str, byte* buffer, int bufferSize)
1370  {
1371  if (str == null)
1372  {
1373  return (byte*) 0;
1374  }
1375 
1376  fixed (char* strPtr = str)
1377  {
1378  Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(strPtr, str.Length + 1, buffer, bufferSize);
1379  }
1380 
1381  return buffer;
1382  }
1383 
1384  /* Used for heap allocated string marshaling.
1385  * Returned byte* must be free'd with FreeHGlobal.
1386  */
1392  internal static unsafe byte* Utf8EncodeHeap(string str)
1393  {
1394  if (str == null)
1395  {
1396  return (byte*) 0;
1397  }
1398 
1399  int bufferSize = Utf8Size(str);
1400  byte* buffer = (byte*) Marshal.AllocHGlobal(bufferSize);
1401  fixed (char* strPtr = str)
1402  {
1403  Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(strPtr, str.Length + 1, buffer, bufferSize);
1404  }
1405 
1406  return buffer;
1407  }
1408 
1409  /* This is public because SDL_DropEvent needs it! */
1416  public static unsafe string UTF8_ToManaged(IntPtr s, bool freePtr = false)
1417  {
1418  if (s == IntPtr.Zero)
1419  {
1420  return null;
1421  }
1422 
1423  /* We get to do strlen ourselves! */
1424  byte* ptr = (byte*) s;
1425  while (*ptr != 0)
1426  {
1427  ptr++;
1428  }
1429 
1430  /* TODO: This #ifdef is only here because the equivalent
1431  * .NET 2.0 constructor appears to be less efficient?
1432  * Here's the pretty version, maybe steal this instead:
1433  *
1434  string result = new string(
1435  (sbyte*) s, // Also, why sbyte???
1436  0,
1437  (int) (ptr - (byte*) s),
1438  System.Text.Encoding.UTF8
1439  );
1440  * See the CoreCLR source for more info.
1441  * -flibit
1442  */
1443 #if NETSTANDARD2_0
1444  /* Modern C# lets you just send the byte*, nice! */
1445  string result = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(
1446  (byte*) s,
1447  (int) (ptr - (byte*) s)
1448  );
1449 #else
1450  /* Old C# requires an extra memcpy, bleh! */
1451  int len = (int) (ptr - (byte*) s);
1452  if (len == 0)
1453  {
1454  return string.Empty;
1455  }
1456 
1457  char* chars = stackalloc char[len];
1458  int strLen = Encoding.UTF8.GetChars((byte*) s, len, chars, len);
1459  string result = new string(chars, 0, strLen);
1460 #endif
1461 
1462  /* Some SDL functions will malloc, we have to free! */
1463  if (freePtr)
1464  {
1465  SDL_free(s);
1466  }
1467 
1468  return result;
1469  }
1470 
1471  #endregion

1483  public static uint SDL_FOURCC(byte a, byte b, byte c, byte d) => (uint) (a | (b << 8) | (c << 16) | (d << 24));
1484

1508  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
1509  internal static extern IntPtr SDL_malloc(IntPtr size);
1510 
1515  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]

1517 
1518  /* Buffer.BlockCopy is not available in every runtime yet. Also,
1519  * using memcpy directly can be a compatibility issue in other
1520  * strange ways. So, we expose this to get around all that.
1521  * -flibit
1522  */
1530  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
1531  public static extern IntPtr SDL_memcpy(IntPtr dst, IntPtr src, IntPtr len);

1671  /* IntPtr refers to an SDL_RWops* */
1678  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_RWFromFile", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]

1683 
1690  public static unsafe IntPtr SDL_RWFromFile(
1691  string file,
1692  string mode
1693  )
1694  {
1695  byte* utf8File = Utf8EncodeHeap(file);
1696  byte* utf8Mode = Utf8EncodeHeap(mode);
1697  IntPtr rwOps = INTERNAL_SDL_RWFromFile(
1698  utf8File,
1699  utf8Mode
1700  );
1701  Marshal.FreeHGlobal((IntPtr) utf8Mode);
1702  Marshal.FreeHGlobal((IntPtr) utf8File);
1703  return rwOps;
1704  }

1973  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_LoadFile", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]

1975 
1982  public static unsafe IntPtr SDL_LoadFile(string file, out IntPtr datasize)
1983  {
1984  byte* utf8File = Utf8EncodeHeap(file);
1985  IntPtr result = INTERNAL_SDL_LoadFile(utf8File, out datasize);
1986  Marshal.FreeHGlobal((IntPtr) utf8File);
1987  return result;
1988  }

3863  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_ShowMessageBox", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
3864  private static extern int INTERNAL_SDL_ShowMessageBox([In] ref InternalSdlMessageBoxData messageboxdata, out int buttonid);
3865 
3866  /* Ripped from Jameson's LpUtf8StrMarshaler */
3872  private static IntPtr INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(string str)
3873  {
3874  if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(str))
3875  {
3876  return IntPtr.Zero;
3877  }
3878 
3879  byte[] bytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(str + '\0');
3880  IntPtr mem = SDL_malloc((IntPtr) bytes.Length);
3881  Marshal.Copy(bytes, 0, mem, bytes.Length);
3882  return mem;
3883  }
3884 
3891  public static unsafe int SDL_ShowMessageBox([In] ref SdlMessageBoxData messageboxdata, out int buttonid)
3892  {
3893  InternalSdlMessageBoxData data = new InternalSdlMessageBoxData
3894  {
3895  flags = messageboxdata.flags,
3896  window = messageboxdata.window,
3897  title = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.title),
3898  message = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.message),
3899  numbuttons = messageboxdata.numbuttons
3900  };
3901 
3902  InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData[] buttons = new InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData[messageboxdata.numbuttons];
3903  for (int i = 0; i < messageboxdata.numbuttons; i++)
3904  {
3905  buttons[i] = new InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData
3906  {
3907  flags = messageboxdata.buttons[i].flags,
3908  buttonid = messageboxdata.buttons[i].buttonid,
3909  text = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.buttons[i].text)
3910  };
3911  }
3912 
3913  if (messageboxdata.colorScheme != null)
3914  {
3915  data.colorScheme = Marshal.AllocHGlobal(Marshal.SizeOf(typeof(SdlMessageBoxColorScheme)));
3916  Marshal.StructureToPtr(messageboxdata.colorScheme.Value, data.colorScheme, false);
3917  }
3918 
3919  int result;
3920  fixed (InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData* buttonsPtr = &buttons[0])
3921  {
3922  data.buttons = (IntPtr) buttonsPtr;
3923  result = INTERNAL_SDL_ShowMessageBox(ref data, out buttonid);
3924  }
3925 
3926  Marshal.FreeHGlobal(data.colorScheme);
3927  for (int i = 0; i < messageboxdata.numbuttons; i++)
3928  {
3929  SDL_free(buttons[i].text);
3930  }
3931 
3932  SDL_free(data.message);
3933  SDL_free(data.title);
3934 
3935  return result;
3936  }

8364  public static uint SDL_DEFINE_PIXELFOURCC(byte a, byte b, byte c, byte d) => SDL_FOURCC(a, b, c, d);
8365 
8375  public static uint SDL_DEFINE_PIXELFORMAT(
8376  SdlPixelType type,
8377  uint order,
8378  SdlPackedLayout layout,
8379  byte bits,
8380  byte bytes
8381  )
8382  => (uint) (
8383  (1 << 28) |
8384  ((byte) type << 24) |
8385  ((byte) order << 20) |
8386  ((byte) layout << 16) |
8387  (bits << 8) |
8388  bytes
8389  );
8390 
8396  public static byte SDL_PIXELFLAG(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 28) & 0x0F);
8397 
8403  public static byte SDL_PIXELTYPE(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 24) & 0x0F);
8404 
8410  public static byte SDL_PIXELORDER(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 20) & 0x0F);
8411 
8417  public static byte SDL_PIXELLAYOUT(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 16) & 0x0F);
8418 
8424  public static byte SDL_BITSPERPIXEL(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 8) & 0xFF);
8425 
8431  public static byte SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL(uint x)
8432  {
8433  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(x))
8434  {
8435  if (x == SdlPixelformatYuy2 ||
8436  x == SdlPixelformatUyvy ||
8437  x == SdlPixelformatYvyu)
8438  {
8439  return 2;
8440  }
8441 
8442  return 1;
8443  }
8444 
8445  return (byte) (x & 0xFF);
8446  }
8447 
8453  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_INDEXED(uint format)
8454  {
8455  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
8456  {
8457  return false;
8458  }
8459 
8460  SdlPixelType pType =
8461  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
8462  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex1 ||
8463  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex4 ||
8464  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex8;
8465  }
8466 
8472  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_PACKED(uint format)
8473  {
8474  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
8475  {
8476  return false;
8477  }
8478 
8479  SdlPixelType pType =
8480  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
8481  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked8 ||
8482  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked16 ||
8483  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked32;
8484  }
8485 
8491  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ARRAY(uint format)
8492  {
8493  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
8494  {
8495  return false;
8496  }
8497 
8498  SdlPixelType pType =
8499  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
8500  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu8 ||
8501  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu16 ||
8502  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu32 ||
8503  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayf16 ||
8504  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayf32;
8505  }
8506 
8512  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ALPHA(uint format)
8513  {
8514  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_PACKED(format))
8515  {
8516  SdlPackedOrder pOrder =
8517  (SdlPackedOrder) SDL_PIXELORDER(format);
8518  return pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderArgb ||
8519  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderRgba ||
8520  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderAbgr ||
8521  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderBgra;
8522  }
8523 
8524  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ARRAY(format))
8525  {
8526  SdlArrayOrder aOrder =
8527  (SdlArrayOrder) SDL_PIXELORDER(format);
8528  return aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderArgb ||
8529  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderRgba ||
8530  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderAbgr ||
8531  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderBgra;
8532  }
8533 
8534  return false;
8535  }
8536 
8542  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(uint format) => (format == 0) && (SDL_PIXELFLAG(format) != 1);

12567 
12568  /* userdata refers to a void* */
12575  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
12576  private static extern SdlBool SDL_GetEventFilter(
12577  out IntPtr filter,
12578  out IntPtr userdata
12579  );
12580 
12587  public static SdlBool SDL_GetEventFilter(
12588  out SdlEventFilter filter,
12589  out IntPtr userdata
12590  )
12591  {
12592  IntPtr result = IntPtr.Zero;
12593  SdlBool retval = SDL_GetEventFilter(out result, out userdata);
12594  if (result != IntPtr.Zero)
12595  {
12596  filter = (SdlEventFilter) Marshal.GetDelegateForFunctionPointer(
12597  result,
12598  typeof(SdlEventFilter)
12599  );
12600  }
12601  else
12602  {
12603  filter = null;
12604  }
12605 
12606  return retval;
12607  }

14140  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_GetScancodeFromName", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
14141  private static extern unsafe SdlScancode INTERNAL_SDL_GetScancodeFromName(

14143  );
14144 
14150  public static unsafe SdlScancode SDL_GetScancodeFromName(string name)
14151  {
14152  int utf8NameBufSize = Utf8Size(name);
14153  byte* utf8Name = stackalloc byte[utf8NameBufSize];
14154  return INTERNAL_SDL_GetScancodeFromName(
14155  Utf8Encode(name, utf8Name, utf8NameBufSize)
14156  );
14157  }

18302 
18312  public static unsafe uint SDL_OpenAudioDevice(
18313  string device,
18314  int iscapture,
18315  ref SdlAudioSpec desired,
18316  out SdlAudioSpec obtained,
18317  int allowedChanges
18318  )
18319  {
18320  int utf8DeviceBufSize = Utf8Size(device);
18321  byte* utf8Device = stackalloc byte[utf8DeviceBufSize];

19359  /* Only available in 2.0.1 or higher. */
19366  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_GetPrefPath", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
19367  private static extern unsafe IntPtr INTERNAL_SDL_GetPrefPath(
19368  byte* org,
19369  byte* app
19370  );
19371 
19378  public static unsafe string SDL_GetPrefPath(string org, string app)
19379  {
19380  int utf8OrgBufSize = Utf8Size(org);
19381  byte* utf8Org = stackalloc byte[utf8OrgBufSize];
19382 
19383  int utf8AppBufSize = Utf8Size(app);
19384  byte* utf8App = stackalloc byte[utf8AppBufSize];
19385 
19386  return UTF8_ToManaged(
19387  INTERNAL_SDL_GetPrefPath(
19388  Utf8Encode(org, utf8Org, utf8OrgBufSize),
19389  Utf8Encode(app, utf8App, utf8AppBufSize)
19390  ),
19391  true
19392  );
19393  }
